obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (39128)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060&sectionId=39128&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Andhra Pradesh and Mysore (Transfer of Territory)`
  line `Act, 1968.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (39129)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060&sectionId=39129&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means the 1st day of October, 1968;`
  line
  line `(b) "assembly constituency", "council constituency" and "parliamentary constituency" have`
  line `the same meanings as in the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950);`
  line
  line `(c) "sitting member", in relation to either House of Parliament or of the Legislature of a State,`
  line `means a person who, immediately before the appointed day, is a member of that House;`
  line
  line `(d) "transferred territory" means the territory specified in the Schedule and transferred from`
  line `the State of Mysore to the State of Andhra Pradesh by section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (39130)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Transfer of territory from Mysore to Andhra Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060&sectionId=39130&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the appointed day,`
  line `there shall be added to the State of Andhra Pradesh the territory specified in the Schedule which shall`
  line `thereupon cease to form part of the State of Mysore.`
  line
  line `(2) The transferred territory shall be included in, and form part of the Hindupur taluk of`
  line `Anantapur district in the State of Andhra Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in sub-section (2) shall be deemed to affect the power of the State Government to`
  line `alter, after the appointed day, the name, extent or boundaries of any district or taluk in the State of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (39131)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Amendment of First Schedule to the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060&sectionId=39131&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, in the First`
  line `Schedule to the Constitution, under the heading "I. THE STATES",—`
  line
  line `(a) for the entry against "I. Andhra Pradesh, the following shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"The territories specified in sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Andhra State Act, 1953,`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3 of the States Reorganisation Act, 1956, the First Schedule to the`
  line `Andhra Pradesh and Madras (Alteration of Boundaries) Act, 1959, and the Schedule to the`
  line `Andhra Pradesh and Mysore (Transfer of Territory) Act, 1968, but excluding the territories`
  line `specified in the Second Schedule to the Andhra Pradesh and Madras (Alteration of`
  line `Boundaries) Act, 1959".; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the entry against "9. Mysore", after the words and figures "States Reorganisation`
  line `Act, 1956", the words, brackets and figures "but excluding the territory specified in the Schedule`
  line `to the Andhra Pradesh and Mysore (Transfer of Territory) Act, 1968" shall be inserted.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (39132)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Extent of parliamentary and assembly Constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060&sectionId=39132&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, the`
  line `transferred territory shall cease to be part of Madhugiri parliamentary constituency and Bagepalli`
  line `assembly constituency in the State of Mysore as delimited in Order No. 11 of the Delimitation`
  line `Commission made under section 10 of the Delimitation Commission Act, 1962 (61 of 1962), and shall`
  line `form part of Hindupur parliamentary constituency and Hindupur assembly constituency in the State of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh as delimited in Order No. 3 of the Delimitation Commission made under the said`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (39133)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Provision as to sitting members of Parliament and Legislative Assemblies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060&sectionId=39133&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The sitting`
  line `members of the House of the People representing Hindupur parliamentary constituency in the State of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh and Madhugiri parliamentary constituency in the State of Mysore shall,`
  line `notwithstanding the alteration in the extent of those constituencies by virtue of the provisions of this`
  line `Act, continue to be members of the House of the People.`
  line
  line `(2) The sitting members of the Legislative Assemblies of Andhra Pradesh and Mysore`
  line `representing Hindupur assembly constituency and Bagepalli assembly constituency respectively shall,`
  line `notwithstanding the alteration in the extent of those constituencies by virtue of the provisions of this`
  line `Act, continue to be members of the said Assemblies.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (39134)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Extent of Council Constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060&sectionId=39134&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any reference in the Delimitation of Council`
  line `Constituencies (Andhra Pradesh) Order, 1957, to Anantapur district shall be construed as including`
  line `the territory transferred to that district from the State of Mysore.`
  line
  line `(2) Any reference in the Delimitation of Council Constituencies (Mysore) Order, 1951, to Kolar`
  line `district shall be construed as excluding the territory transferred from that district to the State of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (39135)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Sitting Members of Legislative Councils.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060&sectionId=39135&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Every sitting member of the Legislative Council`
  line `of Andhra Pradesh or of Mysore representing a council constituency the extent of which is altered by`
  line `virtue of section 7 shall, as from the appointed day, be deemed to have been elected to the said`
  line `Council by that constituency as so altered.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (39136)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Extension of jurisdiction of Andhra Pradesh High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060&sectionId=39136&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the`
  line `appointed day,—`
  line
  line `(a) the jurisdiction of the High Court of Andhra Pradesh shall extend to the transferred`
  line `territory; and`
  line
  line `(b) the High Court of Mysore shall have no jurisdiction in respect of the said territory.`
  line
  line `(2) If, immediately before the appointed day, there is any proceeding relatable to the transferred`
  line `territory pending in the High Court of Mysore, then, notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `sub-section (1), such proceeding shall be heard and disposed of by that High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) Any order made by the High Court of Mysore in any proceeding with respect to which that`
  line `High Court exercises jurisdiction by virtue of sub-section (2) shall, for all purposes, have effect, not`
  line `only as an order of the High Court of Mysore but also as an order made by the High Court of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) proceedings shall be deemed to be pending in the High Court of Mysore until that Court`
  line `has disposed of all issues between the parties, including any issues with respect to the taxation of`
  line `the costs of the proceedings and shall include appeals, applications for leave to appeal to the`
  line `Supreme Court, applications for review, petitions for revision and petitions for writs;`
  line
  line `(b) references to a High Court shall be construed as including references to a Judge or`
  line `division court thereof, and references to an order made by a court or a Judge shall be construed as`
  line `including references to a sentence, judgment or decree passed or made by that court or Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (39147)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Appropriation of moneys for expenditure in transferred territory under existing Appropriation Acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060&sectionId=39147&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, any Act passed by the Legislature of Andhra`
  line `Pradesh before that day for the appropriation of any money out of the Consolidated Fund of the State`
  line `to meet any expenditure in respect of any part of the financial year 1968-69 shall have effect also in`
  line `relation to the transferred territory, and it shall be lawful for the State Government to spend any`
  line `amount for that territory out of the amount authorised by such Act to be expended for any services in`
  line `that State.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (39138)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Assets and liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060&sectionId=39138&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) All land and all stores, articles and other goods in the transferred`
  line `territory belonging to the State of Mysore shall, as from the appointed day, pass to the State of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this sub-section, the expression "land" includes immovable property of every`
  line `kind and any rights in or over such property and the expression "goods" does not include coins, bank`
  line `notes and currency notes.`
  line
  line `(2) All rights, liabilities and obligations, whether arising out of a contract or otherwise, of the`
  line `State of Mysore in relation to the transferred territory shall, as from the appointed day, be the rights,`
  line `liabilities and obligations, respectively, of the State of Andhra Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (39139)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `State Financial Corporations and State Electricity Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060&sectionId=39139&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day,—`
  line
  line `(a) the Financial Corporations constituted under the State Financial Corporations Act, 1951`
  line `(63 of 1951), for the States of Mysore and Andhra Pradesh, and`
  line
  line `(b) the State Electricity Boards constituted under the Electricity (Supply)`
  line `Act, 1948 (54 of 1948), for the said States.`
  line
  line `shall be deemed to have been constituted for those States with their areas as altered by the provisions`
  line `of section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (39140)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Extension of laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060&sectionId=39140&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `All laws which, immediately before the appointed day, extend to, or are`
  line `in force in, the Hindupur taluk of Anantapur district in the State of Andhra Pradesh but do not extend`
  line `to, or are not in force in, the transferred territory, shall, as from that day, extend to, or as the case may`
  line `be, come into force in, the transferred territory; and all laws which, immediately before the appointed`
  line `day, are in force in the transferred territory but not in the Hindupur taluk of Anantapur district in the`
  line `State of Andhra Pradesh shall, on that day, cease to be in force in the transferred territory, except as`
  line `respects things done or omitted to be done before that day.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, "law" includes any enactment, ordinance, regulation, order,`
  line `bye-law, rule, scheme, notification or other instrument having the force of law in the whole or in any`
  line `part of the State of Andhra Pradesh or Mysore.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (39141)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to construe laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060&sectionId=39141&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Any court, tribunal or authority required or empowered to enforce`
  line `any law extended to the transferred territory by section 13 may, for the purpose of facilitating its`
  line `application in relation to the transferred territory, construe the law in such manner, without affecting`
  line `the substance, as may be necessary or proper in regard to the matter before the court, tribunal or`
  line authority.
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (39142)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060&sectionId=39142&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Where, immediately before the appointed day, the State of Mysore is a`
  line `party to any legal proceedings with respect to any property, rights or liabilities transferred to the State`
  line `of Andhra Pradesh under this Act, the State of Andhra Pradesh shall be deemed to be substituted for`
  line `the State of Mysore as a party to those proceedings, or added as a party thereto, as the case may be,`
  line `and the proceedings may continue accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (39143)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Transfer of pending proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060&sectionId=39143&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every proceeding pending immediately before the`
  line `appointed day before any court (other than a High Court), tribunal, authority or officer in any area`
  line `which on that day falls within the State of Mysore shall, if it is a proceeding relating exclusively to`
  line `any part of the transferred territory, stand transferred to the corresponding court, tribunal, authority or`
  line `officer in the State of Andhra Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether any proceeding should stand transferred under`
  line `sub-section (1), it shall be referred to the High Court of Mysore and the decision of that High Court`
  line `shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) In this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) "proceeding" includes any suit, case or appeal; and`
  line
  line `(b) "corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer" in the State of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh means—`
  line
  line `(i) the court, tribunal, authority or officer in which, or before whom, the proceeding`
  line `would have lain if the proceeding had been instituted after the appointed day, or`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of doubt, such court, tribunal, authority or officer in that State as may be`
  line `determined after the appointed day by the Government of Andhra Pradesh, or before the`
  line `appointed day by the Government of Mysore, to be the corresponding court, tribunal,`
  line `authority or officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (39144)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Effect of provisions inconsistent with other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060&sectionId=39144&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have`
  line `effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (39145)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060&sectionId=39145&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act (including any difficulty in relation to the transition under section 13 from one law to another`
  line `law), the President may by order do anything not inconsistent with any such provision which appears`
  line `to him to be necessary for the purpose of removing the difficulty.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (39146)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060&sectionId=39146&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00016_196836_1517807320060
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make rules to give effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or ^1`
  line `[in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid], both Houses agree in making`
  line `any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be, so however`
  line `that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_translations:
